  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">SYSTEMS OF GOVERNMENT<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Presidential System&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">presidential system means a system of government in which a single individual known as president is the Head of State and Head of Government. Here the president plays dual functions of ceremonial and real executive matter. Thus, there is fusion of ceremonial and executive power.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Nigeria, in 1979, first practiced a presidential system of government and Alhaji Shehu Shagari of National Party of Nigeria (NPN) was elected the first indigenous Executive President. Countries like USA, Brazil, Bolivia, Colombia, and Tanzania practice presidential system of government.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Features of Presidential System of Government&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Unification of powers of Head of state and government<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Separation of power<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Supremacy of the constitution<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Presidential veto over law<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Appointment of ministers from nonparty members<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Checks and balances are in operation<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Merits of Presidential System<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Supremacy of the constitution<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Appointment of qualified and competent ministers<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Separation of power<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Stability of government<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Accountability to electorate<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Demerits<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Expensive cost<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Executive-legislative conflict<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Authoritarianism<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Parliamentary System&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Parliamentary System or cabinet system of government exists where the functions of the Head of State are separated from that of the Head of Government and are carried and are carried out by two individuals, the president and the Prime minister respectively.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The parliamentary system is marked for there lack of strict separation of powers between the executive and the legislature but in the presidential system there is total separation of powers.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A Prorogation means a proclamation by the head of state ending a session of parliament, it is the discontinuation of the meeting of a legislative body without dissolving it.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The parliamentary system is marked for their lack of strict separation of powers between the executive and the legislature but in the presidential system there is total separation of powers.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In a presidential and cabinet system of government, the ministers are individually responsible to the president, but the legislature are collectively responsible and thus they share both blame and praise.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A presidential system of government is one where the Head of State possesses real powers.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Features of Parliamentary System<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Dual executive (head of states and head of government)<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Collective responsibility<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Ministers are chosen from the ruling party<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Absence of separation of powers<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Parliamentary supremacy<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Merits of Parliamentary system<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Reduced executive Burden<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Less expensive to operate<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Quick passage of law<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Promotes accountability in government<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Better executive and legislature cooperation.<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Demerits of Parliamentary system<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Political instability<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Distraction of government by opposition party or shadow government in the form of critism and distraction.<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Dispute between President and Prime minister<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Lack of separation of power<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The concept of collective responsibility is synonymous with&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">a. presidential system of government, b. military system of government&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">c. unitary system of government, d. parliamentary system of government.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. Parliamentary system<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">One major factor that differentiates the presidential from the parliamentary system is_____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. separation of powers, B. judicial independence, C. passage of bills, D. party system.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A (2009\/2010, no 7).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">separation of powers<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In a presidential system of government, ministers are____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. individually responsible to the president, B. collectively responsible to the president<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. individually responsible to no one, D collectively responsible to the senate, E. individually and collectively responsible to the electorate<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A (2014\/2015, no 6).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The presidential system differs from the parliamentary system of government in that<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. The principle of collective responsibility applies. B. Executive and legislative powers are fused. C. Powers of the three arms of government are merged. D. The tenure of office of the president is limited<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. Executive and legislative powers are fused<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A proclamation by the Head of State ending a session of parliament is called__.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. a dissolution, B. an adjournment, C. a prorogation, D. an abrogation, E. a devolution<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2014\/2015, no 3).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">a prorogation<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">3. In a parliamentary system, the term shadow cabinet is often used to refer to the____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. back-benchers in the house<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. deputy prime ministers and assistant, ministers<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. rebellious members or the ruling party<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. portfolio designates of the party opposition<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D (2017\/2018, no 3)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A shadow cabinet is an opposition party to the party in government.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Military Government&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The military protect the sovereignty and territorial integrity of a country from external invasion. The military in Nigeria include the army, the Air force and the Navy Military government is the type of government under the control of the armed forces of a state that comes to power through military coup or force.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Military coup is forceful overthrow of government by the armed forces. Coup is a sudden and forcible seizure of government power through illegal and unconstitutional means. The military claim to be a corrective regime. They believe that they come to power to correct the misconducts of politicians.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">However, experience has shown that the military are not less corrupt than civilians. Because military rule is unconstitutional, the first thing that a military government does after successful coup over a civilian government is to suspend the constitution and rule by decree and edict. In military regime, there is fusion of executive and legislative power.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Revolution<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Revolution is not the same thing with coup d&rsquo;&eacute;tat. Revolution is a fundamental or radical change in government as well as socio-economic structure of a state while coup d&rsquo;&eacute;tat is forceful change in government only. Revolution involves mass political action.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Features of Military Rule<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Coup d&rsquo;etat<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Undemocratic<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Rule by decree and edict<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Citizens right can be violated<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Accountability is very poor<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Centralized structure and based on command system.<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Merits of Military Rule<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Quick decision making<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Defense of sovereignty<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Development<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Easy state creation<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Demerits of Military Rule\/Government<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Undemocratic<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Unconstitutional<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Abuse of human Rights<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">No rule of law<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Poor Accountability and absence of separation of power<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Military intervention in Nigeria arose from<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. perceived incapability of civilians to govern, B. international pressure for change<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. the desire for a military government, D. civilian&#39;s desire to relinquish power<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. perceived incapability of civilians to govern,<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first institution introduced by the military to exercise legislative power was the<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. supreme military council, B. armed forces ruling council, C. federal executive council<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. supreme military council<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Laws made by military governments at the state level are called&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. acts, B. decrees, C. bye-laws, D. edicts<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. edicts<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "SYSTEMS OF GOVERNMENT"
}